        "biography": {
            "errors": [],
            "value": "I am a specialized researcher in estimating corporate costs of gender-based violence and designing models for managing and preventing inequitable management patterns in organizations. Over the past 10 years, I have published research on this topic in Spanish, English, and German. I work as an international consultant on equitable management for large and medium-sized companies in Peru, Ecuador, Bolivia, and Paraguay. I have also been a consultant for the German Cooperation Agency GIZ from 2012 to 2023. Additionally, I am the director of the Research Institute at the Faculty of Administrative Sciences and Human Resources at the University of San Martin de Porres since 2012.\nIn terms of teaching, I have experience in research methodology and thesis advising since 2005. I created and coordinated the courses of Applied Business Research I and II (USMP, 2008-2011). I am the author of manuals and methodological guides for developing projects and theses, such as \"Seven Steps to Develop a Thesis\" (Macro Publishing, 2015) and \"How to Evaluate the Scientific Rigor of Doctoral Theses?\" (USMP Publishing, 2010).",
